      "content": "<p style=\"text-align: left;\">The minimum estimated boiling point for normal paraffins corresponds to a paraffin with a molecular weight of <math alttext=\"149.02\"><mn>149.02</mn>\n</math> grams per mole and an estimated boiling point of <math alttext=\"186.05\"><mn>186.05</mn>\n</math> degrees Celsius.</p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "bc51eca9-2eef-4517-ac52-463ed9633864",
      "content": "<p style=\"text-align: left;\">The maximum estimated boiling point for normal paraffins corresponds to a paraffin with a molecular weight of <math alttext=\"149.02\"><mn>149.02</mn>\n</math> grams per mole and an estimated boiling point of <math alttext=\"186.05\"><mn>186.05</mn>\n</math> degrees Celsius.</p>"
    }
  ],
